any type of tinker's table work no need for oak ^^

parts can be replaced, the mattock work as an axe, an hoe and mine dirt but doesn't work as a shovel . (yes it need a shovel part for making it but don't mind i don't understand me too)
we're going to need clay for making our first cast, bucket and our smeltery
let's make some grout for your smeltery !
the clay bucket broke when used with lava be warn ^^
we all know this smelterie and if not tinkers add a nice book to explain everything ^^

copper is the next step for your progression this metal as varius utilisation but the first will be to make a better pick

note that your furnace can't melt down ores you'll need to process them before, then all your fisrt ores will be melted in the tinker's smeltery

the pack contain Agricraft this mean that vanilla agriculture is disable.
Weed is enable in the pack.
let's make some first seed , by breaking grass you will find hemp seed and wheat, you can find riz near rivers lake or ocean your bread it from the previous crops.

the wooden hand rake allow you to take away the weed from your crops,
the clipper to replicate your seed with a chance base on the strenth of the crop, a strenth of 10 mean 100% to your clipping to work it's safer than spreeding crop.
the gardening trowel allow you to move your crops /!\ unfully growth crops won't drop there seeds.
let's upgrade our tools !
Bronze is an alloy made from tin and copper
aluminium brass is made from aluminium and copper it is used to make reusable cast

your lether armor is usefull for the start but let's make a better one !
i've an old trick to help amor to repair by themself i'll just take it 2s

the smeltery is a nice ore processor but not the most efficent one let's start with a bit better one.

the crushing table allow you to crush ores into rocky chunck , then we can clean them in the sluice box and get extra ore.

it also allow you to make plate by placing block or ingot.

the thermal's hammer's works with the crushing table wich take cake of mining level.
the sluice box will allow you to clean your rocky ores and get extra ore with water

let's make a bite of steam to make electricity !

the combustion chamber will burn fuel to make heat the boiler will consume water to make steam a 20 mb/t max, the pipes transfert liquid you need to configure input on pipe with the wrench to make them working

the small steam turbine need 1mb of steam to produce 2J , 1W= 1J/t. cable have an intern resistance making energy lose by passing throug (it's better explain in the book but it just work as real electricty then it's nice)

copper coil have a resistance of  2 Ohm/cable and a max distance of 10 block at 125V

the electric pole work as if it has a resistance a 2.5 Ohm/cable at 125 V but transfert at a higher voltage the pole transformer add 0.25 Ohm to the circuit

you can make your system without making math if you want or if you enjoy electricity you can determine your loss and other nice thing

if your machines needs more energy that your generator can produce a V drop will occur this mean that your voltage will drasticly down (around 65V with only 20W of over consumption) and with the voltage downgrade your loss will raise up.

one block machines share theyre power

eletricity seems to works as if it's continous voltage and not alternative and machines purly resistive component (no need of complex for the math)

right with the blueprint to get a prevew of the multiblock when all black a placed right click again on the block wich looks like a wooden crate in your multiblock and it will form
This new high tech sieve can be automated and process other ore

produce more electricity
